{'book': {'publisher': 'Mirrorstone', 'synopsis': 'This lavishly illustrated guide showcases the wide array of fantastic dragons encountered on the world of Krynn. Sindri Suncatcher–wizard’s apprentice–opens up his personal notebooks to share his knowledge of these awe-inspiring creatures, from the life cycle of a kind copper dragon to the best way to counteract a red dragon’s fiery breath.<br/><br/>The perfect companion to the Dragonlance: The New Adventures series, this beautifully illustrated title introduces readers to the looks and habits of dragons of the Dragonlance world. With tips and tricks every new adventurer can use on imaginary encounters with dragons, this book will enchant readers with both pictures and words.<br/><br/>About the Author<br/>Sindri Suncatcher is a three-and-a-half foot tall kender, who enjoys storytelling, collecting magical tokens, and fighting dragons. He lives in Solamnia and is currently studying magic under the auspices of the black-robed wizard Maddoc. You can catch Sindri in the midst of his latest adventure in The Wayward Wizard.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/16/43/9780786941643.jpg', 'title_long': 'A Practical Guide to Dragons (Practical Guides)', 'edition': 'First Edition', 'dimensions': 'Height: 11.19 Inches, Length: 8.81 Inches, Weight: 1.05 Pounds, Width: 0.47 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.81}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.47}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.05}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 11.19}}, 'pages': 80, 'date_published': '2006-09-26', 'subjects': ['Teen & Young Adult', 'Science Fiction & Fantasy', 'Fantasy', 'Self Service', 'Custom Stores'], 'authors': ['Lisa Trumbauer'], 'title': 'A Practical Guide to Dragons (Practical Guides)', 'isbn13': '9780786941643', 'msrp': 9.89, 'binding': 'Hardcover', 'isbn': '0786941642', 'isbn10': '0786941642'}}